Name: D-arabinose transport via diffusion (extracellular to periplasm)
Gene-Protein-Rule (GPR): KPN_00282 or KPN_00956 or KPN_01445 or KPN_02636
Evidence: Protein purification evidence that Klebsiella can process this substrate which implies it can be imported into the cell. Corresponds to an OMP porin which is known to have four-five genes in the gene-protein-rule (Eg: 23CAMPtex). KPN_00956 (corresponding to ompF) does not have an ortholog in E. coli but does have one in Salmonella (Eg: 2PGtex). Therefore the missing gene has been included into the gene-protein-rule without sequence evidence.
